Let's now calculate the effective semiannual rate of the investment.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Semiannual Rate} &=\dfrac{0.1128}{2}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf5.64\%}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the effective semiannual rate is 5.64%.**

Now, divide the nominal rate by quarterly periods to determine the effective quarterly rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Quarterly Rate} &=\dfrac{0.1113}{4}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf2.78\%}
\end{aligned}$$

**Based on our calculation, the effective quarterly rate of the investment is 2.78%.**

Next, divide the nominal rate by the period to calculate the effective monthly rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Effective Monthly Rate} &=\dfrac{ 0.110254 }{12}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf0.92\%}
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, as can be seen in our calculation, the effective monthly rate of the investment is 0.92%.**
